cs.FL, cs.ET, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata and their descriptional power. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper discusses a relatively new concept of semi-quantum automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper compares the power of semi-quantum automata with that of DFA in terms of size. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible as the paper presents a uniform method for lower bounds on the size of semi-quantum automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also possible as the paper deals with the descriptional power of different models of automata.
